content:
In the wake of the deadly ambush on responding firefighters in Coeur d'Alene, Idaho, the suspect's grandfather spoke to 
@ABC
 News on Monday, sharing his grief for those killed and injured in the attack.

BREAKING: The Senate voted 50-50 on President Trump's megabill, with Vice President JD Vance casting the tie-breaking vote to pass the massive tax and immigration bill.
@jayobtv
 has the latest: https://abcnews.link/h4xhip0

Days before news broke about a plea deal in the case of the Idaho college murders, the siblings of victim Ethan Chapin spoke to 
@ABC
 News to share their story for the first time.

The Trump administration is threatening all of Harvard University's federal funding after it said it found the university to be in "violent violation" of the Civil Rights Act, according to a new letter sent to the university that was viewed by 
@ABC
 News.

A group of Americans who have lost family members to violence perpetrated by drug cartels is urging the Trump administration to designate additional criminal groups as terrorist organizations, according to a letter exclusively obtained by 
@ABC
 News.

Two firefighters were killed and another wounded after gunfire erupted while firefighters responded to a brush fire on the mountain near Coeur d'Alene, Idaho, on Sunday.
@MattGutmanABC
 reports. https://abcnews.link/TA08OD8

It's been nearly a month since Travis Decker went on the run after allegedly killing his three young daughters near a Washington state campground, and at least one expert told 
@ABC
 News he believes the fugitive father is likely still alive.

The Supreme Court ruled that a government task force that determines what preventive health care services insurers must cover, at no cost, under the Affordable Care Act is constitutional.
@ABC
 News' legal contributor James Sample breaks down the ruling. https://abcnews.link/58ZAXvF

"This does have broader implications," 
@rachelvscott
 says, after SCOTUS granted a partial stay of nationwide injunctions issued by district courts against Pres. Trump's executive order to effectively end birthright citizenship.   https://abcnews.link/Re5AdCp

ABC News' 
@WhitJohnson
 and @DevinDwyerABC report as the Supreme Court grants a partial stay of injunctions issued by district courts against President Trump's order to end birthright citizenship. https://abcnews.link/vwRVyDi

The Supreme Court is meeting today to decide the final six cases of its term, including Pres. Trump's bid to enforce his executive order denying birthright citizenship to U.S.-born children of parents who are in the country illegally.
@DevinDwyer
 reports. https://abcnews.link/4HhYlTE

It's been nearly a month since Travis Decker went on the run after allegedly killing his three young daughters near a Washington state campground, and at least one expert told 
@ABC
 News he believes the fugitive father is likely still alive.

EXCLUSIVE: The Trump administration is looking to speed up its ability to fine those in the U.S. illegally — up to $1,000 per day — according to a rule set to be published Friday in the Federal Register that was obtained by 
@ABC
 News.

Lalo Schifrin, a film composer best known for writing the 'Mission: Impossible' theme, has died at the age of 93. 
@DavidMuir
 shares the incredible impact he made on over 100 movie scores. https://abcnews.link/ae0Iv1F

Two teenagers went missing from eastern Idaho, according to local authorities, and their mother says she believes they left with members of the Fundamentalist Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints.
@ABC
 News’ 
@AndreaFujiiTV
 reports. https://abcnews.link/k0m4nrw

Zohran Mamdani tells 
@ABC
 News’ 
@RachelVScott
 that if elected mayor of New York City, he would work with the Trump administration “when it is to the benefit of New Yorkers,” but not “if it comes at the expense of the New Yorkers that I’m running to serve.” https://abcnews.link/StS7Xl1

Pres. Trump said the U.S. would meet with Iran next week as the country's supreme leader made his first public statement since a ceasefire was declared in the war with Israel.
@ABC
 News' 
@JonKarl
 has the latest. https://abcnews.link/ENYyETM

The woman who said she will offer key eyewitness testimony in Bryan Kohberger's capital murder trial repeated that claim at least four times, to three different officers, after she was pulled over last year, per police footage obtained by 
@ABC
 News.

After the stunning results of the Democratic mayoral primary in New York City, 
@rachelvscott
 speaks with Zohran Mamdani, who defeated nearly a dozen candidates, including former New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo. https://abcnews.link/fA4Um0a
